bilingual.source: The therapist diagnosed him as a sado.
bilingual.target: 治疗师诊断他为施虐狂。

bilingual.source: The therapist located the acupoint on my back.
bilingual.target: 治疗师找到了我背上的穴位。

bilingual.source: The therapist helped him unravel his feelings.

bilingual.source: She felt unstuck after talking to her therapist.

bilingual.source: He decided to become a therapist to help others.

bilingual.source: The therapist uses hypnotism to help patients relax.
bilingual.target: 治疗师使用催眠术帮助患者放松。

yingyinNormal.en: You want me to see a therapist?
Maybe you should talk to a therapist about this. Too expensive.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这事你去找咨询师聊聊吧。太贵了。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, maybe he was getting confused him with his childhood therapist.
yingyinNormal.zh: 或许他把他跟他小时候的心理医生搞混了。

yingyinNormal.en: That's not possible. It's more than possible, she was John's therapist.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不可能。怎么不可能，她是约翰的治疗师。

yingyinNormal.en: He saw a therapist? Yeah, he used to have this recurring nightmare, just really freaked him out.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他有心理医生？他以前常常做重复的噩梦，吓死他了。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm picking up Rosie this afternoon, after I've seen my therapist. Got a new one, seeing her today.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我下午见过心理医生之后，会去接萝丝。找了个新的，今天开始去见她。

yingyinNormal.en: How did you know? How? On Monday, I decided to get a new therapist. Tuesday afternoon, I chose her.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你怎么知道的？！怎么知道的？我这周一才决定要换治疗师。周二下午选了她。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, please don't go anywhere, I'm sure the therapist who actually lives her wouldn't want blood on the carpet.
yingyinNormal.zh: 别走，真正住这里的治疗师肯定不希望地毯上溅上血。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, you can hide behind a sexy smile or a walking cane, or just be a therapist, talking about you all the time.
yingyinNormal.zh: 一个性感的微笑或拐杖就能让你隐藏起来，或是做个治疗师，一直聊你的事。

yingyinNormal.en: I need to know my way around your thoughts better than your wife better than your therapist, better than anyone.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我需要了解你的想法，比你的老婆，治疗医师以及其他所有人更了解。

yingyinNormal.en: She needs help, Claire. What do we do? I mean, should we send her back to that therapist? The one we've never met?
yingyinNormal.zh: 她需要帮助，克莱尔，我们该怎么办？我们该再送她去看那个心理医生吗？我们从没见过的那个吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, my God! You sound just like the woman at the interview! Have you ever thought about talking to some kind of therapist about all this? Maybe.
yingyinNormal.zh: 天啊！你说的简直跟面试那女士一样！你有想过去跟什么心理医生之类的谈这事吗？或许吧。
